24/12/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The OSCE's Office for Democratic Institutions and Human Rights announced on Friday (December 22nd) the official launch of its observation mission for Serbia's parliamentary elections, scheduled for January 21st. The mission, led by Ambassador Geert Ahrens, includes ten observers as the core staff in Belgrade. Sixteen long-term observers and 100 short-term ones will be deployed across the country. The vote, the first in Serbia since the breakup of the former state union with Montenegro in May, is considered crucial for Serbia's Euro-Atlantic integration aspirations. (OSCE website, Tanjug - 22/12/06)
